# Repo Codex Brief — VN1

> Forecasting-experiments repo for the VN1 Challenge (weekly retail
> demand, Client × Warehouse × Product, ~13-week horizon). Notebook-first
> sandbox; no service or library surface.

## Current Priorities
- Stabilize the LightGBM starter pipeline against the pinned `lightgbm<4.5` / `ipykernel<7` versions.
- Improve the AutoETS baseline as a sanity reference for any new model.
- Future work (open): hyperparameter search via Optuna, blended ensembles, per-segment models.

## Start Here
- Read `CLAUDE.md` — full project orientation, conventions, and pin rationale.
- Read `.claude/AGENTS.md` for durable repo rules.
- Run `make install` to set up the venv + Jupyter kernel.
- Open `LightGbmStarter.ipynb` (the canonical pipeline) and `AutoETS.ipynb` (the baseline).

## Default Working Mode
- Implementation > speculation.
- Promote stable notebook code into `src/` as typed functions (mirror `src/data.py`).
- Call out blockers, risks, and assumptions explicitly.

## Architecture Preferences
- Polars for transforms; pandas only at library boundaries that demand it.
- `pyproject.toml` + `uv.lock` are the source of truth for dependencies. No `requirements.txt`.
- Pinned versions exist for upstream-bug reasons — do not bump `lightgbm`, `ipykernel`, etc. without verifying the upstream fix.

## Output Preferences
- Concise summaries first.
- Include exact file paths and commands.
- Show verification status (which cell ran, what failed) and any gaps.

## Verification Bias
- This repo has no test suite. Verify by running the affected notebook cells end-to-end and checking that `MLForecast.fit` → `predict` produces the expected output shape.
- `make lint` checks formatting only.

## High-Value Paths
- `LightGbmStarter.ipynb` — primary pipeline.
- `AutoETS.ipynb` — baseline.
- `src/data.py` — shared loaders.
- `pyproject.toml` — dependency pins (read the comments before editing).
- `Makefile` — developer entry points.
- `.claude/wiki/pages/` — knowledge graph (papers, competition rules, competitor solutions).
